{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GwjyGkBTCJHhvpkpwuk1es","type":"tool_result","content":"apiVersion: v1\nitems:\n- apiVersion: v1\n  data:\n    plan.md: \"# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16  \\n**Namespace:**\n      ray  \\n**Status:** DRAFT — for review only. No changes have been applied.\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      1. Current State\\n\\n### Deployments\\n\\n| Deployment | Replicas | Image |\\n|---|---|---|\\n|\n      ray-head | 1 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 |\\n| ray-worker | 3 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n      |\\n\\nBoth deployments have **no resource requests or limits** configured (`resources:\n      {}`), which leaves pods unconstrained and may cause OOM evictions or CPU starvation\n      under load.\\n\\n### Services\\n\\n| Service | Type | Ports |\\n|---|---|---|\\n|\n      ray-head | ClusterIP (10.96.224.130) | 6379/TCP (gcs), 8265/TCP (dashboard)\n      |\\n\\nThe Ray dashboard is exposed on port 8265 of the `ray-head` ClusterIP service.\n      It is reachable only from within the cluster (no NodePort or LoadBalancer).\n      There is no separate dashboard service.\\n\\n### Summary of non-default configuration\n      already in place\\n- Worker replicas scaled up from default 1 → **3**\\n- Dashboard\n      port (8265) added to the `ray-head` Service alongside GCS (6379)\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\\n\\n### 2a. Image Upgrade: 2.9.0\n      → 2.10.0\\n\\nUpgrade both `ray-head` and `ray-worker` from `rayproject/ray:2.9.0`\n      to `rayproject/ray:2.10.0`.  \\nRationale: 2.10 includes runtime environment\n      improvements, autoscaler fixes, and dashboard stability patches relevant to\n      this cluster's usage profile.\\n\\n### 2b. Add Resource Requests and Limits\\n\\nSet\n      explicit CPU/memory budgets to prevent noisy-neighbour evictions and give the\n      scheduler accurate placement information.\\n\\n**ray-head** (GCS server + dashboard;\n      latency-sensitive, not compute-heavy):\\n- requests: cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\\n-\n      limits:   cpu=2,    memory=2Gi\\n\\n**ray-worker** (task execution; may be CPU/memory\n      intensive):\\n- requests: cpu=1,    memory=2Gi\\n- limits:   cpu=4,    memory=4Gi\\n\\n###\n      2c. Scale Workers from 3 → 4\\n\\nAdd a fourth worker replica to increase parallel\n      task throughput and provide headroom during rolling updates (one worker will\n      be temporarily unavailable during the image upgrade rollout).\\n\\n### 2d. Expose\n      Dashboard via a Dedicated NodePort Service\\n\\nCreate a separate `ray-dashboard`\n      NodePort service so the dashboard is reachable from outside the cluster without\n      `kubectl port-forward`. The existing `ray-head` ClusterIP service is left unchanged.\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      3. Proposed kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — review only)\\n\\n### Step 1: Upgrade\n      ray-head image and set resource limits\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray set image\n      deploy/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-head\n      --type=merge -p '{\\n  \\\"spec\\\": {\\n    \\\"template\\\": {\\n      \\\"spec\\\": {\\n\n      \\       \\\"containers\\\": [{\\n          \\\"name\\\": \\\"ray-head\\\",\\n          \\\"resources\\\":\n      {\\n            \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"500m\\\", \\\"memory\\\": \\\"1Gi\\\"},\\n            \\\"limits\\\":\n      \\  {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"2\\\",    \\\"memory\\\": \\\"2Gi\\\"}\\n          }\\n        }]\\n      }\\n\n      \\   }\\n  }\\n}'\\n```\\n\\n### Step 2: Upgrade ray-worker image, set resource limits,\n      and scale to 4 replicas\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker\n      ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-worker --type=merge\n      -p '{\\n  \\\"spec\\\": {\\n    \\\"replicas\\\": 4,\\n    \\\"template\\\": {\\n      \\\"spec\\\":\n      {\\n        \\\"containers\\\": [{\\n          \\\"name\\\": \\\"ray-worker\\\",\\n          \\\"resources\\\":\n      {\\n            \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"1\\\",  \\\"memory\\\": \\\"2Gi\\\"},\\n            \\\"limits\\\":\n      \\  {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"4\\\",  \\\"memory\\\": \\\"4Gi\\\"}\\n          }\\n        }]\\n      }\\n\n      \\   }\\n  }\\n}'\\n```\\n\\n### Step 3: Create dedicated NodePort service for the\n      Ray dashboard\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray apply -f - <<'EOF'\\napiVersion: v1\\nkind:\n      Service\\nmetadata:\\n  name: ray-dashboard\\n  namespace: ray\\n  labels:\\n    app.kubernetes.io/component:\n      dashboard-service\\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\\nspec:\\n  type: NodePort\\n\n      \\ selector:\\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: head\\n    app.kubernetes.io/name:\n      ray\\n    bench.ray.cluster: ray\\n  ports:\\n    - name: dashboard\\n      port:\n      8265\\n      targetPort: 8265\\n      nodePort: 30265\\nEOF\\n```\\n\\n### Step 4:\n      Verify rollout completion\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head\\nkubectl\n      -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker\\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head\n      ray-worker\\nkubectl -n ray get svc\\n```\\n\\n### Rollback (if needed)\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl\n      -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-head\\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-worker\\nkubectl\n      -n ray delete svc ray-dashboard\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Risk Assessment\\n\\n| Risk\n      | Likelihood | Mitigation |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Worker OOMKill during image pull\n      under load | Medium | Scale to 4 replicas before image upgrade so cluster retains\n      capacity |\\n| GCS server restart causes task failures | Low | ray-head rolling\n      update briefly interrupts GCS; schedule in a low-traffic window |\\n| nodePort\n      30265 conflicts with existing allocation | Low | Verify `kubectl get svc -A\n      | grep 30265` before applying |\\n| 2.9 → 2.10 protocol incompatibility | Low\n      | Both head and worker must be upgraded atomically in the same window |\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      5. Validation Checklist (post-upgrade)\\n\\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get deploy`\n      shows ray-head=1/1 and ray-worker=4/4 READY\\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get pods`\n      — all pods Running, no CrashLoopBackOff\\n- [ ] Ray dashboard reachable at `http://<node-ip>:30265`\\n-\n      [ ] Submit a test Ray task and confirm it completes successfully\\n- [ ] `kubectl\n      -n ray top pods` — resource usage within the new limits\\n\"\n  kind: ConfigMap\n  metadata:\n    creationTimestamp: \"2026-06-16T09:44:31Z\"\n    name: change-plan\n    namespace: ray\n    resourceVersion: \"60966\"\n    uid: 2ee3cc00-e5b4-4b1c-9773-9d392bd8ba26\n- apiVersion: v1\n  data:\n    job.py: |\n      import subprocess\n      import ray\n\n      subprocess.run([\"ray\", \"start\", \"--address=ray-head:6379\"], check=True)\n\n      ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")\n\n      print(\"pong\")\n\n      ray.shutdown()\n  kind: ConfigMap\n  metadata:\n    annotations:\n      kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration: |\n        {\"apiVersion\":\"v1\",\"data\":{\"job.py\":\"import ray\\n\\nray.init(address=\\\"ray://ray-head:10001\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"pong\\\")\\n\\nray.shutdown()\\n\"},\"kind\":\"ConfigMap\",\"metadata\":{\"annotations\":{},\"labels\":{\"app.kubernetes.io/component\":\"job-script\",\"app.kubernetes.io/name\":\"ray\",\"bench.ray.cluster\":\"ray\"},\"name\":\"ray-job-script\",\"namespace\":\"ray\"}}\n    creationTimestamp: \"2026-06-16T09:27:33Z\"\n    labels:\n      app.kubernetes.io/component: job-script\n      app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\n      bench.ray.cluster: ray\n    name: ray-job-script\n    namespace: ray\n    resourceVersion: \"60776\"\n    uid: cb9b6eb3-75e8-46f5-80c0-155c87d96c61\nkind: List\nmetadata:\n  resourceVersion: \"\"","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a603893-eff7-4c51-b0af-40db70d285ff","uuid":"d05477e9-9b38-4b45-bcbd-972947fc7a5e","timestamp":"2026-06-16T09:44:59.096Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"apiVersion: v1\nitems:\n- apiVersion: v1\n  data:\n    plan.md: \"# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16  \\n**Namespace:**\n      ray  \\n**Status:** DRAFT — for review only. No changes have been applied.\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      1. Current State\\n\\n### Deployments\\n\\n| Deployment | Replicas | Image |\\n|---|---|---|\\n|\n      ray-head | 1 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0 |\\n| ray-worker | 3 | rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n      |\\n\\nBoth deployments have **no resource requests or limits** configured (`resources:\n      {}`), which leaves pods unconstrained and may cause OOM evictions or CPU starvation\n      under load.\\n\\n### Services\\n\\n| Service | Type | Ports |\\n|---|---|---|\\n|\n      ray-head | ClusterIP (10.96.224.130) | 6379/TCP (gcs), 8265/TCP (dashboard)\n      |\\n\\nThe Ray dashboard is exposed on port 8265 of the `ray-head` ClusterIP service.\n      It is reachable only from within the cluster (no NodePort or LoadBalancer).\n      There is no separate dashboard service.\\n\\n### Summary of non-default configuration\n      already in place\\n- Worker replicas scaled up from default 1 → **3**\\n- Dashboard\n      port (8265) added to the `ray-head` Service alongside GCS (6379)\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\\n\\n### 2a. Image Upgrade: 2.9.0\n      → 2.10.0\\n\\nUpgrade both `ray-head` and `ray-worker` from `rayproject/ray:2.9.0`\n      to `rayproject/ray:2.10.0`.  \\nRationale: 2.10 includes runtime environment\n      improvements, autoscaler fixes, and dashboard stability patches relevant to\n      this cluster's usage profile.\\n\\n### 2b. Add Resource Requests and Limits\\n\\nSet\n      explicit CPU/memory budgets to prevent noisy-neighbour evictions and give the\n      scheduler accurate placement information.\\n\\n**ray-head** (GCS server + dashboard;\n      latency-sensitive, not compute-heavy):\\n- requests: cpu=500m, memory=1Gi\\n-\n      limits:   cpu=2,    memory=2Gi\\n\\n**ray-worker** (task execution; may be CPU/memory\n      intensive):\\n- requests: cpu=1,    memory=2Gi\\n- limits:   cpu=4,    memory=4Gi\\n\\n###\n      2c. Scale Workers from 3 → 4\\n\\nAdd a fourth worker replica to increase parallel\n      task throughput and provide headroom during rolling updates (one worker will\n      be temporarily unavailable during the image upgrade rollout).\\n\\n### 2d. Expose\n      Dashboard via a Dedicated NodePort Service\\n\\nCreate a separate `ray-dashboard`\n      NodePort service so the dashboard is reachable from outside the cluster without\n      `kubectl port-forward`. The existing `ray-head` ClusterIP service is left unchanged.\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      3. Proposed kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — review only)\\n\\n### Step 1: Upgrade\n      ray-head image and set resource limits\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray set image\n      deploy/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-head\n      --type=merge -p '{\\n  \\\"spec\\\": {\\n    \\\"template\\\": {\\n      \\\"spec\\\": {\\n\n      \\       \\\"containers\\\": [{\\n          \\\"name\\\": \\\"ray-head\\\",\\n          \\\"resources\\\":\n      {\\n            \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"500m\\\", \\\"memory\\\": \\\"1Gi\\\"},\\n            \\\"limits\\\":\n      \\  {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"2\\\",    \\\"memory\\\": \\\"2Gi\\\"}\\n          }\\n        }]\\n      }\\n\n      \\   }\\n  }\\n}'\\n```\\n\\n### Step 2: Upgrade ray-worker image, set resource limits,\n      and scale to 4 replicas\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker\n      ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\nkubectl -n ray patch deploy/ray-worker --type=merge\n      -p '{\\n  \\\"spec\\\": {\\n    \\\"replicas\\\": 4,\\n    \\\"template\\\": {\\n      \\\"spec\\\":\n      {\\n        \\\"containers\\\": [{\\n          \\\"name\\\": \\\"ray-worker\\\",\\n          \\\"resources\\\":\n      {\\n            \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"1\\\",  \\\"memory\\\": \\\"2Gi\\\"},\\n            \\\"limits\\\":\n      \\  {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"4\\\",  \\\"memory\\\": \\\"4Gi\\\"}\\n          }\\n        }]\\n      }\\n\n      \\   }\\n  }\\n}'\\n```\\n\\n### Step 3: Create dedicated NodePort service for the\n      Ray dashboard\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray apply -f - <<'EOF'\\napiVersion: v1\\nkind:\n      Service\\nmetadata:\\n  name: ray-dashboard\\n  namespace: ray\\n  labels:\\n    app.kubernetes.io/component:\n      dashboard-service\\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\\nspec:\\n  type: NodePort\\n\n      \\ selector:\\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: head\\n    app.kubernetes.io/name:\n      ray\\n    bench.ray.cluster: ray\\n  ports:\\n    - name: dashboard\\n      port:\n      8265\\n      targetPort: 8265\\n      nodePort: 30265\\nEOF\\n```\\n\\n### Step 4:\n      Verify rollout completion\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head\\nkubectl\n      -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker\\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head\n      ray-worker\\nkubectl -n ray get svc\\n```\\n\\n### Rollback (if needed)\\n\\n```bash\\nkubectl\n      -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-head\\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deploy/ray-worker\\nkubectl\n      -n ray delete svc ray-dashboard\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Risk Assessment\\n\\n| Risk\n      | Likelihood | Mitigation |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Worker OOMKill during image pull\n      under load | Medium | Scale to 4 replicas before image upgrade so cluster retains\n      capacity |\\n| GCS server restart causes task failures | Low | ray-head rolling\n      update briefly interrupts GCS; schedule in a low-traffic window |\\n| nodePort\n      30265 conflicts with existing allocation | Low | Verify `kubectl get svc -A\n      | grep 30265` before applying |\\n| 2.9 → 2.10 protocol incompatibility | Low\n      | Both head and worker must be upgraded atomically in the same window |\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n      5. Validation Checklist (post-upgrade)\\n\\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get deploy`\n      shows ray-head=1/1 and ray-worker=4/4 READY\\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ray get pods`\n      — all pods Running, no CrashLoopBackOff\\n- [ ] Ray dashboard reachable at `http://<node-ip>:30265`\\n-\n      [ ] Submit a test Ray task and confirm it completes successfully\\n- [ ] `kubectl\n      -n ray top pods` — resource usage within the new limits\\n\"\n  kind: ConfigMap\n  metadata:\n    creationTimestamp: \"2026-06-16T09:44:31Z\"\n    name: change-plan\n    namespace: ray\n    resourceVersion: \"60966\"\n    uid: 2ee3cc00-e5b4-4b1c-9773-9d392bd8ba26\n- apiVersion: v1\n  data:\n    job.py: |\n      import subprocess\n      import ray\n\n      subprocess.run([\"ray\", \"start\", \"--address=ray-head:6379\"], check=True)\n\n      ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")\n\n      print(\"pong\")\n\n      ray.shutdown()\n  kind: ConfigMap\n  metadata:\n    annotations:\n      kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration: |\n        {\"apiVersion\":\"v1\",\"data\":{\"job.py\":\"import ray\\n\\nray.init(address=\\\"ray://ray-head:10001\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"pong\\\")\\n\\nray.shutdown()\\n\"},\"kind\":\"ConfigMap\",\"metadata\":{\"annotations\":{},\"labels\":{\"app.kubernetes.io/component\":\"job-script\",\"app.kubernetes.io/name\":\"ray\",\"bench.ray.cluster\":\"ray\"},\"name\":\"ray-job-script\",\"namespace\":\"ray\"}}\n    creationTimestamp: \"2026-06-16T09:27:33Z\"\n    labels:\n      app.kubernetes.io/component: job-script\n      app.kubernetes.io/name: ray\n      bench.ray.cluster: ray\n    name: ray-job-script\n    namespace: ray\n    resourceVersion: \"60776\"\n    uid: cb9b6eb3-75e8-46f5-80c0-155c87d96c61\nkind: List\nmetadata:\n  resourceVersion: \"\"","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
