{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y63vwtUduiHnjuGv2cNfT1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017CAu4Uq9XXUDSKxkw3sZa1","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\n================================================================================\nRAY CLUSTER CONFIGURATION AUDIT\nNamespace : ray\nDate      : 2026-06-16\nAuditor   : Read-only inspection (no cluster changes made)\n================================================================================\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1. WORKER REPLICA COUNT\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nDeployment : ray-worker\nCurrent    : 3 replicas (3/3 Ready)\nBaseline   : 2 replicas (from last-applied-configuration annotation)\nStatus     : DEVIATED — scaled up from 2 → 3\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n2. IMAGE VERSIONS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nray-head   : rayproject/ray:2.9.0  (imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent)\nray-worker : rayproject/ray:2.9.0  (imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent)\nBaseline   : rayproject/ray:2.9.0 for both (unchanged)\nStatus     : NO CHANGE — images are at the originally deployed tag\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n3. RESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nray-head   : resources: {}  (no requests or limits)\nray-worker : resources: {}  (no requests or limits)\nBaseline   : resources: {}  (same as baseline — pre-existing gap)\nStatus     : NON-DEFAULT — no resource governance on either deployment.\n             Pods run as BestEffort QoS class; risk of OOM eviction and\n             CPU starvation under concurrent workloads.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n4. RAY-HEAD DEPLOYMENT — COMMAND CHANGE (dashboard)\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nOriginal command (from last-applied-configuration, revision 1):\n  ray start --head ... --include-dashboard=false --num-cpus=0 --block\n\nCurrent command (revision 2, active):\n  ray start --head ... --include-dashboard=true \\\n    --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0 --num-cpus=0 --block\n\nExposed container ports:\n  6379/TCP  gcs       (original)\n  8265/TCP  dashboard (ADDED in revision 2)\n\nDeployment generation : 2 (patched once after initial deploy)\nStatus     : DEVIATED — dashboard was off at baseline, now enabled and\n             bound on all interfaces (0.0.0.0).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n5. SERVICES\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nService    : ray-head\nType       : ClusterIP (10.96.224.130) — cluster-internal only\nPorts (current):\n  6379/TCP  gcs        (present at baseline)\n  8265/TCP  dashboard  (ADDED — not in last-applied-configuration)\nStatus     : DEVIATED — dashboard port 8265 added to ray-head Service.\n             Dashboard is reachable from within the cluster but NOT\n             externally (no NodePort or LoadBalancer; no ingress observed).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n6. CONFIGMAPS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nkube-root-ca.crt   : System-injected CA bundle. Standard / expected.\n\nchange-plan        : Contains a proposed upgrade plan (plan.md).\n                     Documents intended future changes:\n                       • Image upgrade 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n                       • Add resource requests/limits\n                       • Scale workers 3 → 4\n                       • Add dedicated ray-dashboard NodePort service\n                     Status: DRAFT ONLY — no changes have been applied.\n                     Compliance note: plan ConfigMap is visible to any\n                     pod in the namespace with default RBAC; consider\n                     restricting access if plan contains sensitive detail.\n\nray-job-script     : Contains job.py. Current content DIFFERS from the\n                     last-applied-configuration:\n                       Original : ray.init(address=\"ray://ray-head:10001\")\n                       Current  : adds subprocess call to\n                                  `ray start --address=ray-head:6379`\n                                  before ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")\n                     Status: DEVIATED — job script was modified in-place\n                     after initial apply. The use of port 10001 (Ray\n                     client server) was replaced with port 6379 (GCS).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n7. OTHER RUNNING PODS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\ncurl-test   : 1/1 Running, age ~21 min. Utility/test pod; no controller.\nray-client  : 1/1 Running, age ~2 min. Ray client pod; no controller.\n\nNeither pod is part of a Deployment or StatefulSet. They will not be\nrestarted if evicted. Compliance note: ephemeral test pods should be\ncleaned up after use to reduce attack surface.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n8. SUMMARY OF DEVIATIONS FROM BASELINE\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n#  Component               Baseline          Current           Risk\n-- ----------------------- ----------------- ----------------- --------\n1  ray-worker replicas     2                 3                 Low\n2  ray-head dashboard cmd  disabled (false)  enabled (0.0.0.0) Medium\n3  ray-head container port 6379 only         6379+8265         Medium\n4  ray-head Service ports  6379 only         6379+8265         Medium\n5  ray-job-script job.py   ray://...:10001   gcs ...:6379      Low\n6  resources (both)        {} (pre-existing) {} (unchanged)    High\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n9. COMPLIANCE NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nCRITICAL\n  C1. Resource requests and limits are absent on both deployments.\n      Set CPU/memory requests+limits before the next change window\n      to prevent BestEffort evictions and noisy-neighbour starvation.\n      Suggested starting values are documented in the change-plan CM.\n\nHIGH\n  H1. Ray dashboard is exposed on 0.0.0.0:8265 inside the pod and\n      advertised on the ray-head ClusterIP service. The dashboard\n      provides unauthenticated access to cluster state and job\n      submission by default in Ray 2.x. Restrict access via:\n        (a) NetworkPolicy limiting port 8265 to authorised pods, OR\n        (b) Enable Ray dashboard authentication (--dashboard-password),\n            OR\n        (c) Remove the dashboard Service port if external access is\n            not required and use kubectl port-forward for ad-hoc access.\n\nMEDIUM\n  M1. imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent on a mutable tag (2.9.0) means\n      nodes may run different image digests if the tag is re-pushed.\n      Pin to a digest or use imagePullPolicy: Always for production.\n  M2. Ephemeral pods curl-test and ray-client lack controllers; clean\n      them up post-testing to reduce surface area.\n  M3. change-plan ConfigMap is world-readable within the namespace.\n      If the plan contains operational detail, restrict with RBAC.\n\nLOW\n  L1. ray-job-script was modified after initial apply. Track config\n      changes in version control or via GitOps to maintain an auditable\n      change history.\n  L2. Worker scale-up (2→3) and dashboard enablement appear deliberate\n      per the change-plan CM, but were applied without a corresponding\n      update to the last-applied-configuration label (they were patched\n      directly). Future changes should be applied via kubectl apply with\n      a maintained manifest to keep annotations in sync.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\nEND OF AUDIT REPORT\n================================================================================\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5522,"cache_read_input_tokens":29701,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5522},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a603893-eff7-4c51-b0af-40db70d285ff","uuid":"de20e721-dc1f-4c0e-a4b7-73ae73ad4995","request_id":"req_011Cc6iwxaBu2KW2sysJ4Ux3"}
